invasive /ɪnˈveɪsɪv/

ADJ You use invasive to describe something undesirable that spreads very quickly and that is very difficult to stop from spreading. (令人不快的事物) 迅速扩散的 

例： They found invasive cancer during a routine examination. 他们在一次例行检查中发现了扩散的癌细胞。 

2. ADJ An invasive medical procedure involves operating on a patient or examining the inside of their body. 开刀的 

例： Many people find the idea of any kind of invasive surgery unbearable. 许多人觉得任何一种开刀手术都是难以忍受的。

